This paper is about word embedding composition, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. The paper proposes a generative model that captures specific syntactic relations between words and uses tensor decomposition to improve the composition of word embeddings. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and related topics. 

The second most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes a new method for improving word embedding composition using machine learning techniques. 

The third likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper proposes a new method for improving NLP tasks using AI techniques. 

The fourth likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper uses neural network models to generate word embeddings and improve their composition. 

The fifth likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper deals with the analysis of correlations between words and their embeddings, which can be seen as a network analysis problem.
